A stampede during the annual pilgrimage to Mecca on  Monday killed 182 people, according to a Turkish official at the scene.
They were trampled to death during a ritual known as "stoning the devil"  in Mina, a town 10 kilometres (six miles) from Mecca, Mehmet Nuri Yilmaz told  the Turkish news agency Anatolia.
Yilmaz, a religious affairs official, said Saudi security forces had  sealed off the area.
The Saudi authorities have confirmed a stampede took place without giving  a toll.
